🎯 ROUND 1: OS QUESTIONS (INTERVIEW STYLE)
🧠 Q1: What happens when you run a program?

👉 Think first…

✅ Answer (Perfect Interview Answer)

When we run a program:

1️⃣ OS creates a process
2️⃣ Loads program from disk → RAM
3️⃣ Assigns PID & PCB
4️⃣ CPU starts execution

👉 So program becomes an active process

🧠 Q2: What is the difference between process and thread?

👉 Think…

✅ Answer

A process is an independent execution unit with its own memory,
while a thread is a lightweight unit inside a process that shares memory.

🧠 Q3: What is deadlock and how to prevent it?
✅ Answer

Deadlock is a situation where processes wait for each other in a circular manner.

It can be prevented by breaking one of the four conditions:

Mutual exclusion
Hold and wait
No preemption
Circular wait
🧠 Q4: What is paging and why is it used?
✅ Answer

Paging is a memory management technique where processes are divided into fixed-size pages and mapped to frames in RAM.

It is used to avoid external fragmentation and improve memory utilization.

🎯 ROUND 2: COA QUESTIONS
🧠 Q5: What are the main components of CPU?
✅ Answer

CPU consists of:

ALU → performs calculations
Control Unit → controls execution
Registers → store temporary data
🧠 Q6: What is pipelining?
✅ Answer

Pipelining is a technique where multiple instructions are executed simultaneously by overlapping stages like fetch, decode, and execute.

It improves CPU performance.

🧠 Q7: What is cache memory and why is it needed?
✅ Answer

Cache is a small, fast memory located near CPU.

It stores frequently used data to reduce memory access time and improve performance.

🧠 Q8: What is CPI?
✅ Answer

CPI (Cycles Per Instruction) is the average number of clock cycles required to execute one instruction.

Lower CPI means better performance.

🎯 ROUND 3: SCENARIO QUESTIONS (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥)
🧠 Q9

Two threads update same variable and result is incorrect. Why?

✅ Answer

This is due to race condition, caused by lack of synchronization in critical section.

🧠 Q10

System becomes very slow due to frequent page faults. What is it?

✅ Answer

This is thrashing, where system spends more time swapping pages than executing.

